&lt;p&gt;THE HILLINDON HOSPITALS NHS FOUNDATION TRUST&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;JUNIOR CLINICAL FELLOW x 1&lt;br /&gt;IN GENERAL SURGERY (GENERAL and COLORECTAL or BREAST)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Fixed Term Post for 6 - 12 Months&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This post will work at FY2 / CT1-2 level within the General Surgery department. Although the posts are not recognised as a training posts, the post holder will be included in training and teaching programmes offered to our existing surgical training posts. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The junior doctor will be responsible for day to day ward patient duties, attending the MDT and Radiology meetings. Assistance in day surgery lists is encouraged. They will be supported in this by the other General Surgical doctors in the team which includes consultants and other junior surgical doctors. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Participation in the on-call SHO General Surgery rota will be required.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Hillingdon Hospital Foundation Trust is situated in Uxbridge, with Uxbridge station being the nearest underground linked to the hospital via bus routes. There is limited parking (charge payable) on site. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This post is not recognised for training and full registration with the GMC will be required to undertake this position.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cei Oakley, Senior Service Manager&lt;br /&gt;01895 279 303&lt;/p&gt;
